<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EEC) No 3578/92 of 7 December 1992 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 on the granting of aids for transport by rail, road and inland waterway </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 3578/92, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 toetuste andmise kohta raudtee-, maantee- ja siseveetranspordile 7. detsember 1992 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 75 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 75, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 (4) provides that Member States may promote the development of combined transport by granting aid relating to investment in infrastructure and in the fixed and moveable facilities necessary for transhipment or to the running costs of an intra-Community combined transport service in transit across the territory of non-member countries; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 (4) s&auml;testatakse, et liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad edendada kombineeritud transpordi arengut, andes toetusi, mis on seotud infrastruktuuriinvesteeringutega ning investeeringutega &uuml;mberlaadimiseks vajalikesse paiksetesse v&otilde;i teisaldatavatesse vahenditesse, v&otilde;i kolmandate riikide territooriumide kaudu osutatava &uuml;hendusesisese kombineeritud transporditeenuse ekspluatatsioonikuludega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the evolution of combined transport shows that for the Community as a whole the starting-up phase of this technology has not been completed yet, and whereas the aid arrangements should therefore be maintained for a further period; </inglise>
<eesti> kombineeritud transpordi areng n&auml;itab, et &uuml;henduse jaoks tervikuna ei ole selle tehnoloogia k&auml;ivitusperiood veel l&otilde;ppenud ning seep&auml;rast tuleks toetuste andmist teatava aja jooksul j&auml;tkata; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the possibility of granting such aid for the running costs of combined transport services crossing the territory of a non-member country is warranted only in the specific cases of Austria, Switzerland and the States of the former Yugoslavia; </inglise>
<eesti> toetuste andmine m&otilde;ne kolmanda riigi territooriumit l&auml;bivate kombineeritud transporditeenuste jooksvate kulude katmiseks on p&otilde;hjendatud ainult teatavatel Austria, &Scaron;veitsi ja endise Jugoslaavia riikidega seotud erijuhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the need to achieve economic and social cohesion rapidly in the Community entails putting the emphasis on investment in rail and road facilities specific to combined transport, in particular where they present an aternative to infrastructure work that cannot be completed in the short term; </inglise>
<eesti> &uuml;henduses majandusliku ja sotsiaalse &uuml;htekuuluvuse kiire saavutamise vajadusega kaasneb vajadus edendada investeeringuid kombineeritud transpordile omastesse raudtee- ja maanteerajatistesse, eelk&otilde;ige juhul, kui need on alternatiiviks infrastruktuuridega seotud meetmetele, mida ei ole v&otilde;imalik l&otilde;pule viia l&uuml;hikese aja jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in addition, providing aid for road facilities specific to combined transport would be an effective way of encouraging small and medium-sized undertakings to avail themselves of combined transport services; </inglise>
<eesti> toetuste andmine kombineeritud transpordile omastele maanteerajatistele aitaks t&otilde;husalt motiveerida v&auml;ikesi ja keskmise suurusega ettev&otilde;tteid kasutama kombineeritud transporditeenuseid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas aid for equipment specific to combined transport would foster the development of new bimodal and transhipment technology; </inglise>
<eesti> toetuste andmine kombineeritud transpordi eriseadmetele soodustaks uue bimodaalse tehnoloogia ja &uuml;mberlaadimistehnoloogia arendamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas during a limited start-up phase the possibility of granting aid should therefore be extended to investment in transport facilities specifically designed for combined transport, provided that they are used exclusively for that purpose; </inglise>
<eesti> seep&auml;rast tuleks piiratud k&auml;ivitusperioodi jooksul v&otilde;imaldada toetusi ka investeeringutele spetsiaalselt kombineeritud transpordi jaoks kavandatud transpordirajatistesse, tingimusel et neid kasutatakse ainult kombineeritud transpordis; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the present aid arrangements should be maintained in force until 31 December 1995 and the Council should decide, under the conditions laid down in the Treaty, on the arrangements to be applied subsequently or, if necessary, on the conditions for terminating such aid; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev toetuste andmise kord peaks kehtima 31. detsembrini 1995 ning n&otilde;ukogu peaks asutamislepingus s&auml;testatud tingimuste kohaselt otsustama, millist korda edaspidi kohaldatakse v&otilde;i, kui see on vajalik, millistel tingimustel toetuste andmine l&otilde;petatakse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 should therefore be amended, </inglise>
<eesti> seep&auml;rast tuleks m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 muuta, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Item 1 (e) of Article 3 of Regulation (EEC) No 1107/70 is hereby replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1107/70 artikli 3 l&otilde;ike 1 punkt e asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> '(e) until 31 December 1995, where the aids are granted as a temporary measure and are designed to facilitate the development of combined transport, such aids must relate to: </inglise>
<eesti> "e) kuni 31. detsembrini 1995 juhul, kui toetust antakse ajutiselt ja see on m&otilde;eldud kombineeritud transpordi arendamise h&otilde;lbustamiseks; sellised toetused peavad olema seotud: </eesti>
<inglise> - investment in infrastructure, </inglise>
<eesti> - investeerimisega infrastruktuuri, </eesti>
<inglise> or </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - investment in fixed and moveable facilities necessary for transhipment, </inglise>
<eesti> - investeerimisega &uuml;mberlaadimiseks vajalikesse paiksetesse v&otilde;i teisaldatavatesse vahenditesse, </eesti>
<inglise> or </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - investment in transport equipment specifically designed for combined transport and used exclusively in combined transport, </inglise>
<eesti> - investeerimisega spetsiaalselt kombineeritud transpordi jaoks kavandatud ja ainult kombineeritud transpordis kasutatavatesse seadmetesse, </eesti>
<inglise> or </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - costs of running combined transport services in transit across Austria, Switzerland or the States of the former Yugoslavia. </inglise>
<eesti> - Austria, &Scaron;veitsi v&otilde;i endise Jugoslaavia riikide kaudu osutatavate kombineeritud transporditeenuste ekspluatatsioonikuludega. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall submit a progress report on the above measures to the Council every two years giving details, inter alia, of the destination of the aids, their amount and their impact on combined transport. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon esitab n&otilde;ukogule iga kahe aasta j&auml;rel eespool nimetatud meetmeid k&auml;sitleva arenguaruande, mis kirjeldab muu hulgas toetuste kasutamist, suurust ja m&otilde;ju kombineeritud transpordile. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall supply the Commission with the information needed to compile the report. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid esitavad komisjonile aruande koostamiseks vajaliku teabe. </eesti>
<inglise> By 31 December 1995 the Council, acting on a proposal from the Commission, shall decide under the conditions laid down in the Treaty, on the arrangements to be applied subsequently or, if necessary, on the conditions for terminating them. </inglise>
<eesti> N&otilde;ukogu teeb 31. detsembriks 1995 komisjoni ettepanekul ja asutamislepingus s&auml;testatud tingimuste kohaselt otsuse, millist korda edaspidi kohaldatakse v&otilde;i, kui see on vajalik, millistel tingimustel toetuste andmine l&otilde;petatakse." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from 1 January 1993. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse alates 1. jaanuarist 1993. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 7 December 1992. </inglise>
